### Component 2: Agent 0 Commander ([agent_0_commander.py](file:///C:/Users/User/OneDrive/Desktop/projects/Crypto-trading-bot/backend/src/agents/agent_0_commander.py))
#### [MODIFY] [agent_0_commander.py](file:///c:/Users/User/OneDrive/Desktop/projects/Crypto-trading-bot/backend/src/agents/agent_0_commander.py)

**New Methods:**

| Method | Description |
|---|---|
| `process_telegram_command(text, user_id)` | Entry point. LLM translates freeform text → structured intent |
| `_parse_intent_with_llm(text)` | Claude Haiku translates "dial back risk" → `{action: "REDUCE_RISK", params: {}}` |
| `_assess_proposal_with_agents(intent)` | Gathers Agent 6 macro view + Agent 7 current state to build a briefing |
| `_send_approval_request(briefing, action, user_id)` | Sends Telegram message + stores to `pending_approvals` |
| `_auto_apply_defensive(action, user_id)` | Directly applies reducing risk/pausing without approval |
| `resolve_approval(proposal_id, approved)` | Called from TelegramBot polling when user replies `/approve` or `/reject` |

**Semi-Autonomous Logic:**

```
Defensive moves (LOWER risk, PAUSE trading) → auto-apply, notify you after
Offensive moves (RAISE risk/limits)         → require your /approve or /reject
```

**Strategic Review** enhancement:
- After Sonnet produces its order, it now also provides `agent_votes` (what Agent 6 macro regime says, what Agent 7 risk state says)
- These are included in every Telegram message so you always know *why* Agent 0 is proposing something.

